# Cursor Rules for Filter Website

## Color Token System - MANDATORY

This project uses semantic color tokens. **Never use hardcoded colors.**

### Border Classes
- **CORRECT**: `border-border-default`
- **WRONG**: `border-border`, `border-gray-200`, `border-gray-100`

### Background Classes
- **CORRECT**: `bg-background`, `bg-surface`, `bg-surface-elevated`
- **WRONG**: `bg-white`, `bg-gray-50`, `bg-gray-100`

### Text Classes
- **CORRECT**: `text-primary`, `text-text-secondary`
- **WRONG**: `text-gray-900`, `text-gray-500`, `text-black`

### Quick Reference

| Hardcoded | Replace With |
|-----------|--------------|
| `bg-white` | `bg-background` |
| `bg-gray-50`, `bg-gray-100` | `bg-surface` |
| `border-gray-200`, `border-border` | `border-border-default` |
| `text-gray-900`, `text-black` | `text-primary` |
| `text-gray-500`, `text-gray-600` | `text-text-secondary` |

### Why This Matters
- Ensures dark mode works correctly
- Dark mode uses warm brown tones, not cold grays
- CSS variables auto-switch between light/dark themes

